The article is a statement by the President on Indonesia's ratification of the Comprehensive Test Ban Treaty (CTBT). The President welcomes Indonesia's ratification and highlights it as an example of positive leadership in preventing the spread of nuclear weapons. The CTBT is seen as critical in preventing proliferation and the President urges all states to sign and ratify it. The United States is fully committed to pursuing ratification and will continue to engage with the Senate on its importance to U.S. security. The President emphasizes the need for America to lead the global effort in preventing proliferation, with the early entry into force of the CTBT being a vital part of that effort.